53String Engine::cachesRootPath(const WebCore::ClientOrigin& origin)
54{
55 if (!shouldPersist() || !m_salt)
56 return { };
57
58 Key key(origin.topOrigin.toString(), origin.clientOrigin.toString(), { }, { }, salt());
59 return FileSystem::pathByAppendingComponent(rootPath(), key.hashAsString());
60}
61
62Engine::~Engine()
63{
64 for (auto& caches : m_caches.values())
65 caches->detach();
66
67 auto pendingClearCallbacks = WTFMove(m_pendingClearCallbacks);
68 for (auto& callback : pendingClearCallbacks)
69 callback(Error::Internal);
70
71 auto initializationCallbacks = WTFMove(m_initializationCallbacks);
72 for (auto& callback : initializationCallbacks)
73 callback(Error::Internal);
74
75 auto writeCallbacks = WTFMove(m_pendingWriteCallbacks);
76 for (auto& callback : writeCallbacks.values())
77 callback(Error::Internal);
78
79 auto readCallbacks = WTFMove(m_pendingReadCallbacks);
80 for (auto& callback : readCallbacks.values())
81 callback(Data { }, 1);
82}
83
84void Engine::from(NetworkProcess& networkProcess, PAL::SessionID sessionID, Function<void(Engine&)>&& callback)
85{
86 if (auto* engine = networkProcess.findCacheEngine(sessionID)) {
87 callback(*engine);
88 return;
89 }
90
91 networkProcess.cacheStorageRootPath(sessionID, [networkProcess = makeRef(networkProcess), sessionID, callback = WTFMove(callback)] (auto&& rootPath) mutable {
92 callback(networkProcess->ensureCacheEngine(sessionID, [&] {
93 return adoptRef(*new Engine { sessionID, networkProcess.get(), WTFMove(rootPath) });
94 }));
95 });
96}
97
98void Engine::destroyEngine(NetworkProcess& networkProcess, PAL::SessionID sessionID)
99{
100#if !USE(SOUP) && !USE(CURL)
101 // cURL and Soup based ports destroy the default session right before the process exits to avoid leaking
102 // network resources like the cookies database.
103 ASSERT(sessionID != PAL::SessionID::defaultSessionID());
104#endif
105
106 networkProcess.removeCacheEngine(sessionID);
107}

201static uint64_t getDirectorySize(const String& directoryPath)
202{
203 ASSERT(!isMainRunLoop());
204
205 uint64_t directorySize = 0;
206 Deque<String> paths;
207 paths.append(directoryPath);
208 while (!paths.isEmpty()) {
209 auto path = paths.takeFirst();
210 if (FileSystem::fileType(path) == FileSystem::FileType::Directory) {
211 auto fileNames = FileSystem::listDirectory(path);
212 for (auto& fileName : fileNames) {
213 // Files in /Blobs directory are hard link.
214 if (fileName == "Blobs")
215 continue;
216 paths.append(FileSystem::pathByAppendingComponent(path, fileName));
217 }
218 continue;
219 }
220 directorySize += FileSystem::fileSize(path).value_or(0);
221 }
222 return directorySize;
223}
224
225uint64_t Engine::diskUsage(const String& rootPath, const WebCore::ClientOrigin& origin)
226{
227 ASSERT(!isMainRunLoop());
228
229 if (rootPath.isEmpty())
230 return 0;
231
232 String saltPath = FileSystem::pathByAppendingComponent(rootPath, "salt"_s);
233 auto salt = FileSystem::readOrMakeSalt(saltPath);
234 if (!salt)
235 return 0;
236
237 Key key(origin.topOrigin.toString(), origin.clientOrigin.toString(), { }, { }, *salt);
238 String directoryPath = FileSystem::pathByAppendingComponent(rootPath, key.hashAsString());
239
240 String sizeFilePath = Caches::cachesSizeFilename(directoryPath);
241 if (auto recordedSize = readSizeFile(sizeFilePath))
242 return *recordedSize;
243
244 return getDirectorySize(directoryPath);
245}

247void Engine::requestSpace(const WebCore::ClientOrigin& origin, uint64_t spaceRequested, CompletionHandler<void(WebCore::StorageQuotaManager::Decision)>&& callback)
248{
249 ASSERT(isMainThread());
250
251 if (!m_networkProcess)
252 callback(WebCore::StorageQuotaManager::Decision::Deny);
253
254 RefPtr<WebCore::StorageQuotaManager> storageQuotaManager = m_networkProcess->storageQuotaManager(m_sessionID, origin);
255 if (!storageQuotaManager)
256 callback(WebCore::StorageQuotaManager::Decision::Deny);
257
258 storageQuotaManager->requestSpaceOnMainThread(spaceRequested, WTFMove(callback));
259}

270void Engine::open(const WebCore::ClientOrigin& origin, const String& cacheName, CacheIdentifierCallback&& callback)
271{
272 readCachesFromDisk(origin, [cacheName, callback = WTFMove(callback)](CachesOrError&& cachesOrError) mutable {
273 if (!cachesOrError.has_value()) {
274 callback(makeUnexpected(cachesOrError.error()));
275 return;
276 }
277
278 cachesOrError.value().get().open(cacheName, WTFMove(callback));
279 });
280}
281
282void Engine::remove(uint64_t cacheIdentifier, CacheIdentifierCallback&& callback)
283{
284 Caches* cachesToModify = nullptr;
285 for (auto& caches : m_caches.values()) {
286 auto* cacheToRemove = caches->find(cacheIdentifier);
287 if (cacheToRemove) {
288 cachesToModify = caches.get();
289 break;
290 }
291 }
292 if (!cachesToModify) {
293 callback(makeUnexpected(Error::Internal));
294 return;
295 }
296
297 cachesToModify->remove(cacheIdentifier, WTFMove(callback));
298}

346
347void Engine::initialize(CompletionCallback&& callback)
348{
349 if (m_clearTaskCounter || !m_pendingClearCallbacks.isEmpty()) {
350 m_pendingClearCallbacks.append(WTFMove(callback));
351 return;
352 }
353
354 if (m_salt) {
355 callback(std::nullopt);
356 return;
357 }
358
359 if (!shouldPersist()) {
360 m_salt = NetworkCache::Salt { };
361 callback(std::nullopt);
362 return;
363 }
364
365 bool shouldComputeSalt = m_initializationCallbacks.isEmpty();
366 m_initializationCallbacks.append(WTFMove(callback));
367
368 if (!shouldComputeSalt)
369 return;
370
371 m_ioQueue->dispatch([this, weakThis = makeWeakPtr(this), rootPath = m_rootPath.isolatedCopy()] () mutable {
372 FileSystem::makeAllDirectories(rootPath);
373 String saltPath = FileSystem::pathByAppendingComponent(rootPath, "salt"_s);
374 RunLoop::main().dispatch([this, weakThis = WTFMove(weakThis), salt = FileSystem::readOrMakeSalt(saltPath)]() mutable {
375 if (!weakThis)
376 return;
377
378 m_salt = WTFMove(salt);
379
380 auto callbacks = WTFMove(m_initializationCallbacks);
381 for (auto& callback : callbacks)
382 callback(m_salt ? std::nullopt : std::make_optional(Error::WriteDisk));
383 });
384 });
385}
386
387void Engine::readCachesFromDisk(const WebCore::ClientOrigin& origin, CachesCallback&& callback)
388{
389 initialize([this, origin, callback = WTFMove(callback)](std::optional<Error>&& error) mutable {
390 if (error) {
391 callback(makeUnexpected(error.value()));
392 return;
393 }
394
395 auto& caches = m_caches.ensure(origin, [&origin, this] {
396 auto path = cachesRootPath(origin);
397 return Caches::create(*this, WebCore::ClientOrigin { origin }, WTFMove(path));
398 }).iterator->value;
399
400 if (caches->isInitialized()) {
401 callback(std::reference_wrapper<Caches> { *caches });
402 return;
403 }
404
405 caches->initialize([callback = WTFMove(callback), caches](std::optional<Error>&& error) mutable {
406 if (error) {
407 callback(makeUnexpected(error.value()));
408 return;
409 }
410
411 callback(std::reference_wrapper<Caches> { *caches });
412 });
413 });
414}
415
416void Engine::readCache(uint64_t cacheIdentifier, CacheCallback&& callback)
417{
418 auto* cache = this->cache(cacheIdentifier);
419 if (!cache) {
420 callback(makeUnexpected(Error::Internal));
421 return;
422 }
423 if (!cache->isOpened()) {
424 cache->open([this, protectedThis = makeRef(*this), cacheIdentifier, callback = WTFMove(callback)](std::optional<Error>&& error) mutable {
425 if (error) {
426 callback(makeUnexpected(error.value()));
427 return;
428 }
429
430 auto* cache = this->cache(cacheIdentifier);
431 if (!cache) {
432 callback(makeUnexpected(Error::Internal));
433 return;
434 }
435 ASSERT(cache->isOpened());
436 callback(std::reference_wrapper<Cache> { *cache });
437 });
438 return;
439 }
440 callback(std::reference_wrapper<Cache> { *cache });
441}
442
443Cache* Engine::cache(uint64_t cacheIdentifier)
444{
445 Cache* result = nullptr;
446 for (auto& caches : m_caches.values()) {
447 if ((result = caches->find(cacheIdentifier)))
448 break;
449 }
450 return result;
451}
452
453void Engine::writeFile(const String& filename, NetworkCache::Data&& data, WebCore::DOMCacheEngine::CompletionCallback&& callback)
454{
455 if (!shouldPersist()) {
456 callback(std::nullopt);
457 return;
458 }
459
460 m_pendingWriteCallbacks.add(++m_pendingCallbacksCounter, WTFMove(callback));
461 m_ioQueue->dispatch([this, weakThis = makeWeakPtr(this), identifier = m_pendingCallbacksCounter, data = WTFMove(data), filename = filename.isolatedCopy()]() mutable {
462
463 String directoryPath = FileSystem::parentPath(filename);
464 if (!FileSystem::fileExists(directoryPath))
465 FileSystem::makeAllDirectories(directoryPath);
466
467 auto channel = IOChannel::open(filename, IOChannel::Type::Create, WorkQueue::QOS::Default);
468 channel->write(0, data, WorkQueue::main(), [this, weakThis = WTFMove(weakThis), identifier](int error) mutable {
469 ASSERT(RunLoop::isMain());
470 if (!weakThis)
471 return;
472
473 auto callback = m_pendingWriteCallbacks.take(identifier);
474 if (error) {
475 RELEASE_LOG_ERROR(CacheStorage, "CacheStorage::Engine::writeFile failed with error %d", error);
476
477 callback(Error::WriteDisk);
478 return;
479 }
480 callback(std::nullopt);
481 });
482 });
483}
484
485void Engine::readFile(const String& filename, CompletionHandler<void(const NetworkCache::Data&, int error)>&& callback)
486{
487 if (!shouldPersist()) {
488 callback(Data { }, 0);
489 return;
490 }
491
492 m_pendingReadCallbacks.add(++m_pendingCallbacksCounter, WTFMove(callback));
493 m_ioQueue->dispatch([this, weakThis = makeWeakPtr(this), identifier = m_pendingCallbacksCounter, filename = filename.isolatedCopy()]() mutable {
494 auto channel = IOChannel::open(filename, IOChannel::Type::Read);
495 if (!channel->isOpened()) {
496 RunLoop::main().dispatch([this, weakThis = WTFMove(weakThis), identifier]() mutable {
497 if (!weakThis)
498 return;
499
500 m_pendingReadCallbacks.take(identifier)(Data { }, 0);
501 });
502 return;
503 }
504
505 channel->read(0, std::numeric_limits<size_t>::max(), WorkQueue::main(), [this, weakThis = WTFMove(weakThis), identifier](const Data& data, int error) mutable {
506 RELEASE_LOG_ERROR_IF(error, CacheStorage, "CacheStorage::Engine::readFile failed with error %d", error);
507
508 // FIXME: We should do the decoding in the background thread.
509 ASSERT(RunLoop::isMain());
510
511 if (!weakThis)
512 return;
513
514 m_pendingReadCallbacks.take(identifier)(data, error);
515 });
516 });
517}
518
519void Engine::removeFile(const String& filename)
520{
521 if (!shouldPersist())
522 return;
523
524 m_ioQueue->dispatch([filename = filename.isolatedCopy()]() mutable {
525 FileSystem::deleteFile(filename);
526 });
527}
528
529void Engine::writeSizeFile(const String& path, uint64_t size, CompletionHandler<void()>&& completionHandler)
530{
531 ASSERT(RunLoop::isMain());
532
533 if (!shouldPersist())
534 return completionHandler();
535
536 m_ioQueue->dispatch([path = path.isolatedCopy(), size, completionHandler = WTFMove(completionHandler)]() mutable {
537 Locker locker { globalSizeFileLock };
538 auto fileHandle = FileSystem::openFile(path, FileSystem::FileOpenMode::Write);
539
540 if (FileSystem::isHandleValid(fileHandle)) {
541 FileSystem::truncateFile(fileHandle, 0);
542
543 auto value = String::number(size).utf8();
544 FileSystem::writeToFile(fileHandle, value.data(), value.length());
545
546 FileSystem::closeFile(fileHandle);
547 }
548
549 RunLoop::main().dispatch(WTFMove(completionHandler));
550 });
551}
552
553std::optional<uint64_t> Engine::readSizeFile(const String& path)
554{
555 ASSERT(!RunLoop::isMain());
556
557 Locker locker { globalSizeFileLock };
558 auto fileHandle = FileSystem::openFile(path, FileSystem::FileOpenMode::Read);
559 auto closeFileHandle = makeScopeExit([&] {
560 FileSystem::closeFile(fileHandle);
561 });
562
563 if (!FileSystem::isHandleValid(fileHandle))
564 return std::nullopt;
565
566 auto fileSize = FileSystem::fileSize(path).value_or(0);
567 if (!fileSize)
568 return std::nullopt;
569
570 unsigned bytesToRead;
571 if (!WTF::convertSafely(fileSize, bytesToRead))
572 return std::nullopt;
573
574 // FIXME: No reason we need a heap buffer to read an arbitrary number of bytes when we only support small files that contain numerals.
575 Vector<char> buffer(bytesToRead);
576 unsigned totalBytesRead = FileSystem::readFromFile(fileHandle, buffer.data(), buffer.size());
577 if (totalBytesRead != bytesToRead)
578 return std::nullopt;
579
580 return parseInteger<uint64_t>({ buffer.data(), totalBytesRead });
581}
582
583class ReadOriginsTaskCounter : public RefCounted<ReadOriginsTaskCounter> {
584public:
585 static Ref<ReadOriginsTaskCounter> create(CompletionHandler<void(Vector<WebsiteData::Entry>)>&& callback)
586 {
587 return adoptRef(*new ReadOriginsTaskCounter(WTFMove(callback)));
588 }
589
590 ~ReadOriginsTaskCounter()
591 {
592 m_callback(WTFMove(m_entries));
593 }
594
595 void addOrigin(WebCore::SecurityOriginData&& origin, uint64_t size)
596 {
597 m_entries.append(WebsiteData::Entry { WTFMove(origin), WebsiteDataType::DOMCache, size });
598 }
599
600private:
601 explicit ReadOriginsTaskCounter(CompletionHandler<void(Vector<WebsiteData::Entry>)>&& callback)
602 : m_callback(WTFMove(callback))
603 {
604 }
605
606 CompletionHandler<void(Vector<WebsiteData::Entry>)> m_callback;
607 Vector<WebsiteData::Entry> m_entries;
608};
609
610void Engine::getDirectories(CompletionHandler<void(const Vector<String>&)>&& completionHandler)
611{
612 m_ioQueue->dispatch([path = m_rootPath.isolatedCopy(), completionHandler = WTFMove(completionHandler)]() mutable {
613 Vector<String> folderPaths;
614 for (auto& fileName : FileSystem::listDirectory(path)) {
615 auto filePath = FileSystem::pathByAppendingComponent(path, fileName);
616 if (FileSystem::fileType(filePath) == FileSystem::FileType::Directory)
617 folderPaths.append(filePath.isolatedCopy());
618 }
619
620 RunLoop::main().dispatch([folderPaths = WTFMove(folderPaths), completionHandler = WTFMove(completionHandler)]() mutable {
621 completionHandler(folderPaths);
622 });
623 });
624}
625
626void Engine::fetchEntries(bool shouldComputeSize, CompletionHandler<void(Vector<WebsiteData::Entry>)>&& completionHandler)
627{
628 if (!shouldPersist()) {
629 auto entries = WTF::map(m_caches, [] (auto& pair) {
630 return WebsiteData::Entry { pair.value->origin().clientOrigin, WebsiteDataType::DOMCache, 0 };
631 });
632 completionHandler(WTFMove(entries));
633 return;
634 }
635
636 getDirectories([this, weakThis = makeWeakPtr(this), path = m_rootPath.isolatedCopy(), shouldComputeSize, completionHandler = WTFMove(completionHandler)](const auto& folderPaths) mutable {
637 if (!weakThis)
638 return completionHandler({ });
639 fetchDirectoryEntries(shouldComputeSize, folderPaths, WTFMove(completionHandler));
640 });
641}
642
643void Engine::fetchDirectoryEntries(bool shouldComputeSize, const Vector<String>& folderPaths, CompletionHandler<void(Vector<WebsiteData::Entry>)>&& completionHandler)
644{
645 auto taskCounter = ReadOriginsTaskCounter::create(WTFMove(completionHandler));
646 for (auto& folderPath : folderPaths) {
647 Caches::retrieveOriginFromDirectory(folderPath, *m_ioQueue, [protectedThis = makeRef(*this), shouldComputeSize, taskCounter] (auto&& origin) mutable {
648 ASSERT(RunLoop::isMain());
649 if (!origin)
650 return;
651
652 if (!shouldComputeSize) {
653 taskCounter->addOrigin(WTFMove(origin->topOrigin), 0);
654 taskCounter->addOrigin(WTFMove(origin->clientOrigin), 0);
655 return;
656 }
657
658 protectedThis->readCachesFromDisk(origin.value(), [origin = origin.value(), taskCounter = WTFMove(taskCounter)] (CachesOrError&& result) mutable {
659 if (!result.has_value())
660 return;
661 taskCounter->addOrigin(WTFMove(origin.topOrigin), 0);
662 taskCounter->addOrigin(WTFMove(origin.clientOrigin), result.value().get().storageSize());
663 });
664 });
665 }
666}
667
668CompletionHandler<void()> Engine::createClearTask(CompletionHandler<void()>&& completionHandler)
669{
670 ++m_clearTaskCounter;
671 return [this, protectedThis = makeRef(*this), completionHandler = WTFMove(completionHandler)]() mutable {
672 completionHandler();
673 if (!--m_clearTaskCounter) {
674 auto callbacks = WTFMove(m_pendingClearCallbacks);
675 for (auto& callback : callbacks)
676 initialize(WTFMove(callback));
677 }
678 };
679}
680
681void Engine::clearAllCaches(CompletionHandler<void()>&& completionHandler)
682{
683 ASSERT(RunLoop::isMain());
684
685 auto callbackAggregator = CallbackAggregator::create([this, completionHandler = createClearTask(WTFMove(completionHandler))]() mutable {
686 if (!this->shouldPersist())
687 return completionHandler();
688
689 this->clearAllCachesFromDisk(WTFMove(completionHandler));
690 });
691
692 for (auto& caches : m_caches.values())
693 caches->clear([callbackAggregator] { });
694}
695
696void Engine::clearAllCachesFromDisk(CompletionHandler<void()>&& completionHandler)
697{
698 ASSERT(RunLoop::isMain());
699
700 m_ioQueue->dispatch([path = m_rootPath.isolatedCopy(), completionHandler = WTFMove(completionHandler)]() mutable {
701 Locker locker { globalSizeFileLock };
702 for (auto& fileName : FileSystem::listDirectory(path)) {
703 auto filePath = FileSystem::pathByAppendingComponent(path, fileName);
704 if (FileSystem::fileType(filePath) == FileSystem::FileType::Directory)
705 FileSystem::deleteNonEmptyDirectory(filePath);
706 }
707 RunLoop::main().dispatch(WTFMove(completionHandler));
708 });
709}
710
711void Engine::clearCachesForOrigin(const WebCore::SecurityOriginData& origin, CompletionHandler<void()>&& completionHandler)
712{
713 ASSERT(RunLoop::isMain());
714
715 auto callbackAggregator = CallbackAggregator::create([this, origin, completionHandler = createClearTask(WTFMove(completionHandler))]() mutable {
716 if (!this->shouldPersist())
717 return completionHandler();
718
719 this->clearCachesForOriginFromDisk(origin, [completionHandler = WTFMove(completionHandler)]() mutable {
720 completionHandler();
721 });
722 });
723
724 for (auto& keyValue : m_caches) {
725 if (keyValue.key.topOrigin == origin || keyValue.key.clientOrigin == origin)
726 keyValue.value->clear([callbackAggregator] { });
727 }
728}
729
730void Engine::clearCachesForOriginFromDisk(const WebCore::SecurityOriginData& origin, CompletionHandler<void()>&& completionHandler)
731{
732 ASSERT(RunLoop::isMain());
733 getDirectories([this, weakThis = makeWeakPtr(this), origin, completionHandler = WTFMove(completionHandler)](const auto& folderPaths) mutable {
734 if (!weakThis)
735 return completionHandler();
736 clearCachesForOriginFromDirectories(folderPaths, origin, WTFMove(completionHandler));
737 });
738}
739
740void Engine::clearCachesForOriginFromDirectories(const Vector<String>& folderPaths, const WebCore::SecurityOriginData& origin, CompletionHandler<void()>&& completionHandler)
741{
742 auto callbackAggregator = CallbackAggregator::create(WTFMove(completionHandler));
743 for (auto& folderPath : folderPaths) {
744 Caches::retrieveOriginFromDirectory(folderPath, *m_ioQueue, [this, protectedThis = makeRef(*this), origin, callbackAggregator, folderPath] (std::optional<WebCore::ClientOrigin>&& folderOrigin) mutable {
745 if (!folderOrigin)
746 return;
747 if (folderOrigin->topOrigin != origin && folderOrigin->clientOrigin != origin)
748 return;
749
750 // If cache salt is initialized and the paths do not match, some cache files have probably be removed or partially corrupted.
751 ASSERT(!m_salt || folderPath == cachesRootPath(*folderOrigin));
752 deleteNonEmptyDirectoryOnBackgroundThread(folderPath, [callbackAggregator = WTFMove(callbackAggregator)] { });
753 });
754 }
755}
756
757void Engine::deleteNonEmptyDirectoryOnBackgroundThread(const String& path, CompletionHandler<void()>&& completionHandler)
758{
759 ASSERT(RunLoop::isMain());
760
761 m_ioQueue->dispatch([path = path.isolatedCopy(), completionHandler = WTFMove(completionHandler)]() mutable {
762 Locker locker { globalSizeFileLock };
763 FileSystem::deleteNonEmptyDirectory(path);
764
765 RunLoop::main().dispatch(WTFMove(completionHandler));
766 });
767}
768
769void Engine::clearMemoryRepresentation(const WebCore::ClientOrigin& origin, WebCore::DOMCacheEngine::CompletionCallback&& callback)
770{
771 readCachesFromDisk(origin, [callback = WTFMove(callback)](CachesOrError&& result) mutable {
772 if (!result.has_value()) {
773 callback(result.error());
774 return;
775 }
776 result.value().get().clearMemoryRepresentation();
777 callback(std::nullopt);
778 });
779}
780
781void Engine::lock(uint64_t cacheIdentifier)
782{
783 auto& counter = m_cacheLocks.ensure(cacheIdentifier, []() {
784 return 0;
785 }).iterator->value;
786
787 ++counter;
788}
789
790void Engine::unlock(uint64_t cacheIdentifier)
791{
792 auto lockCount = m_cacheLocks.find(cacheIdentifier);
793 if (lockCount == m_cacheLocks.end())
794 return;
795
796 ASSERT(lockCount->value);
797 if (--lockCount->value)
798 return;
799
800 auto* cache = this->cache(cacheIdentifier);
801 if (!cache)
802 return;
803
804 cache->dispose();
805}
806
807String Engine::representation()
808{
809 ASSERT(m_pendingClearCallbacks.isEmpty());
810 ASSERT(m_initializationCallbacks.isEmpty());
811
812 bool isFirst = true;
813 StringBuilder builder;
814 builder.append("{ \"path\": \"");
815 builder.append(m_rootPath);
816 builder.append("\", \"origins\": [");
817 for (auto& keyValue : m_caches) {
818 if (!isFirst)
819 builder.append(",");
820 isFirst = false;
821
822 builder.append("\n{ \"origin\" : { \"topOrigin\" : \"");
823 builder.append(keyValue.key.topOrigin.toString());
824 builder.append("\", \"clientOrigin\": \"");
825 builder.append(keyValue.key.clientOrigin.toString());
826 builder.append("\" }, \"caches\" : ");
827 keyValue.value->appendRepresentation(builder);
828 builder.append("}");
829 }
830 builder.append("]}");
831 return builder.toString();
832}
